                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Office of the Jewish Messenger</placeName>,</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>119 West Houston Street</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Aug. 7. 1864</date>.</p>\n            <p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Esteemed Sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\"><persName>M. Crehange</persName> a<lb/> member of the central\n                committee of the<lb/> “Universal Israelite Alliance” is<lb/> in <placeName>New\n                    York</placeName> on a brief visit and has<lb/> requested me to furnish him\n                such<lb/> statistical matter, reports, &amp;c. relative<lb/> to the Israelites of\n                the <placeName>United States</placeName><lb/> as might prove of interest &amp; value\n                to<lb/> the archives of the Alliance.<lb/> May I ask that you will kindly<lb/>\n                forward to me (this week, if possible,<lb/> as <persName>Mr Crehange</persName>\n                leaves about the <date>17th</date>.)<lb/> any documents of this character\n                con<lb/>cerning the Israelites of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>,<lb/> such as\n                reports of the Education Society,<lb/> Foster Home, &amp;c.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3qn5zx8h/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
