                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3qn5zx8h/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">It is greatly to be regretted that<lb/> a session of the Board of\n                Delegates<lb/> is again rendered impracticable this<lb/> summer, by the presence of\n                war and<lb/> the difficulty of communicating<lb/> with members of the Board. I<lb/>\n                presume all that the committee<lb/> can do is to continue acting, should occasion\n                demand it, and do all<lb/> in its power for the promotion of<lb/> the objects of the\n                Board. I had<lb/> expected the receipt of a document<lb/> you proposed drafting\n                &amp; forwarding<lb/> to the <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> members for signature<lb/>\n                so that congregations throughout the<lb/> Union may be reminded of the<lb/> duty of\n                sending delegates; but I<lb/> suppose you considered it inopportune<lb/> and\n                therefore delayed its preparation.<lb/> Any request you have to make of<lb/> me with\n                reference to the Board<lb/> will be readily &amp; cheerfully acted</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3qn5zx8h/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
